snippet.textDisplay:
I have a bad history with these eraser sponges.
One time, I dyed my hair red, and some of the dye got on my forehead. My mother was in a really bad mood and didn’t want me going out with the blood-looking dye on my head.
So! First she tried baby oil and cloth to get it off. That didn’t work.
Next! She got the great idea to use baby oil and a mr. clean magic eraser sponge! It hurt like the dickens, but I fought through the pain.
It wasn’t until my mom was almost done that my sister came by and exclaimed that the skin on my forehead was basically melting off. My mother promptly ceased usage of said eraser
My forehead was quite tender and scabby for many days after that event. It was awful!
Thanks for reading my story!
